The text discusses different opinions about life in the future.

The optimistic view says that people will solve serious problems with better healthcare and technology. Life expectancy may increase to around 100 years, people could stay healthier, and new body parts might be grown. Education, technology, and robots could also help reduce problems connected with world population and wealth.

The pessimistic view focuses on possible dangers such as overpopulation, climate change, unemployment caused by robots, and privacy issues
